                 <font color="#FFFFFF"> <li><strong>Megola's Solves Water Problems Without Harming the Environment </strong></li></font>                <font color="#FFFFFF">  <li><strong>Megola is Positioning Themselves as an Acquisition Target</strong></li></font>
                  <font color="#FFFFFF"><li><strong>Banning of Salt Softners </strong></li></font>
                </ul>                </td>
            </tr>
          </table>          <p align="center"><strong>MGOA acquiring control in German Company that owns rights and PATENTS to ScaleGuard technology</strong></p>
          <p>In accordance with Megola's business plan and under the terms of the agreement, Megola Inc. will own 70% of Megola GmbH, with the remaining 30% held by the founders of the German company. Megola GmbH will continue to act as the research and development arm of Megola Inc. , developing new technologies and products for the world market.</p>
          <p>Megola also rolls out with new product lines and is testing the ``IonClear System'', which is an electronic, non-chemical means to disinfect and treat water fouled with contaminants such as bacteria and algae. Trials will take place at an oil field in Northern China as well as a community swimming pool and an industrial cooling water system in Ontario. The <em>IonClear </em> system eliminates the need for conventional biocides and algaecides through the use of copper ionization technology. This technology will eliminate the need for chlorine and OTHER biocides used to treat algae and bacteria. </p>
